  "text": "We studied selected genetic requirements for nuclear envelope fusion in vivo and developed a cell-free assay that reproduces some of these features [CITATION_1] . Tightly membraneassociated proteins required for nuclear membrane fusion after mating (karyogamy or KAR gene products) are involved in the in vivo fusion reaction. In contrast, proteins required for vesicular docking and fusion (Sec18p or N-ethylmaleimide-sensitive factor [NSF] and Sec17p or soluble NSF attachment protein a [m-SNAP]) are not required for homotypic fusion.",
